(Module 1 - Measurements, Vectors and Motion) Tj
T*
(Physical quantity: measurable property. Fundamental quantities include length, mass and) Tj
T*
(time. Derived quantities include velocity, force and pressure.) Tj
T*
(Errors: absolute error = |measured - true|; relative error = absolute error / true) Tj
T*
(value; percentage error = relative error x 100.) Tj
T*
(Vectors: Ax = A cos theta, Ay = A sin theta, R = sqrt\(A^2 + B^2 + 2AB cos theta\).) Tj
T*
(Motion: v = u + at; s = ut + 1/2 at^2; v^2 = u^2 + 2as.) Tj
T*
(Newton laws: inertia, F = ma, action and reaction. Momentum p = mv. Impulse = Ft.) Tj
T*
(Momentum conservation explains recoil of gun and rocket propulsion.) Tj
ET
endstream
endobj
4 0 obj
<< /Length 676 >>
stream
BT
/F1 11 Tf
50 790 Td
14 TL
(Module 2 - Circular Motion and Rotation) Tj
T*
(Angular quantities: omega = theta/t, alpha = change in omega/time. Relation: v = r omega) Tj
T*
(and a = r alpha.) Tj
T*
(Centripetal acceleration ac = v^2/r = r omega^2. Centripetal force Fc = mv^2/r.) Tj
T*
(Banking of roads: tan theta = v^2/rg. Banking reduces skidding on curves.) Tj
T*
(Moment of inertia: I = sum mr^2. Radius of gyration: I = Mk^2.) Tj
T*
(Common MI: rod centre ML^2/12, rod end ML^2/3, ring MR^2, disc MR^2/2, solid sphere) Tj
T*
(2MR^2/5.) Tj
T*
(Torque = rF sin theta. Angular momentum L = I omega. If external torque is zero, angular) Tj
T*
(momentum is conserved.) Tj
ET
endstream
endobj
